{
  "texts": [
    "The relation between kinematics and lensing is especially worth noting.",
    "We have seen earlier (Eq.",
    "(42)) that for a point lens, θ E is proportional to the orbital speed squared.",
    "We now see that an expression like (63) relating θ E and the velocity dispersion is a consequence of the virial theorem.",
    "A relation of this type can always be set up for any lens in dynamical equilibrium, but the precise coefficient depends on details of the mass distribution."
  ]
}